-- India's Reliance Comm shares fall as earnings disappoint
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Sun May 04, 2014 11:53PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 5 (Reuters) - Shares in India's Reliance Communications Ltd <RLCM.NS> fell as much as 2.7 percent on Monday after the mobile carrier's consolidated net profit dropped more than expected in the January-March quarter.

Reliance Communications, controlled by billionaire Anil Ambani, said late on Friday consolidated net profit fell 48.5 percent to 1.56 billion rupees ($26 million) for its fourth quarter, from 3.03 billion rupees reported a year earlier. [ID:nL3N0NO3NC]